    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Study of religious doctrines and practices as understood within a particular religious tradition, usually from the viewpoint of committed religious believers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000032741/Peterson's Guide to Graduate and Professional Programs (1967-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estudio de doctrinas y prácticas religiosas como comprensión dentro de una tradición religiosa particular, usualmente desde el punto de vista de creyentes religiosos comprometidos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De studie van godsdienstige dogma's en gebruiken zoals die uit een bepaalde religieuze traditie kunnen worden afgeleid, meestal gezien vanuit het oogpunt van overtuigde gelovigen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
